s an RMP Reportable Incident [40 CFR 68.42]: In the five-year accident history Zinus USA Inc will report all accidental releases from covered processes that resulted in deaths, injuries, or significant property damage onsite, or known offsite deaths, injuries, evacuations, sheltering in place, property damage, or environmental damage. For each accidental release included, Zinus USA Inc. shall report the following information:

¿  Date, time, and approximate duration of the release;
¿  Chemical(s) released;
¿  Estimated quantity released in pounds, and for mixtures containing regulated toxic substances, percentage concentration by weight of the released regulated toxic substance in the liquid mixture;
¿  Five- or six-digit North American Industry Classification System code for process;
¿  The type of release event and its source;
¿  Weather conditions, if known;
¿  Onsite impacts;
¿  Known offsite impacts;
¿  Initiating event and contributing factors if known;
¿  Whether offsite responders were notified if known; and
¿  Operational or process changes that resulted from investigation of the release and that have been made by the time this information is submitted to the RMP*eSubmit system.

  Per 40 CFR 68.195(a), the information listed in the data requirements section above will be updated by Zinus USA Inc. in Section 6 in the RMP*eSubmit system within 6 months of the release or by the time the RMP is updated as required by 68.190, whichever is earlier.  Additionally, incident investigation information contained in Section 8 (RMP Program 2) of the RMP*eSubmit system must be updated within 6 months of the release or by the time the RMP is updated as required by 68.190, whichever is earlier.

5. The Emergency Response Program

